  "A composite function is formed when one function is applied to the result of another, written as (f o g)(x) = f(g(x)). The chain rule is specifically designed for differentiating composite functions.": "复合函数是当一个函数应用到另一个函数的结果时形成的,其写法为(f o(g)(x) = f(g(x) ) = f(g)(x) 。 链规则是专门为区分复合函数而设计的。",
